== History ==
=== Nakatsu Castle in the Meiji Restoration Period ===
[[File:中津城Tenshu.jpg|thumb|right|Nakatsu Castle’s reconstructed tenshu]]

In August 1863 (Bunkyū 3), the southern part of Nakatsu Castle’s main keep was developed into the “Pine Palace,” which housed princesses returning from the domain’s Edo residence.<ref name="Pine Palace Info">Informational Signboard “Pine Palace,” Nakatsu City, Historical Society of Nakatsu</ref> After the 1871 (Meiji 4) {{ill|Abolition of the han system|ja|廃藩置県|12=draft}}, the Pine Palace was repurposed as the Nakatsu City Hall under the {{ill|Kokura Prefecture|ja|小倉県|12=draft}} administration and later served as the Nakatsu Branch of Ōita Prefecture.<ref name="Pine Palace Info"/>

During the {{ill|Satsuma Rebellion|ja|西南戦争|12=draft}}, dissatisfied samurai from the former Nakatsu Domain formed the {{ill|Nakatsu Corps|ja|中津隊|12=draft}} and burned the Pine Palace on March 31, 1877.<ref name="Pine Palace Info"/>

=== Establishment of Nakatsu Daijingu and Nakatsu Shrine ===
